<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
  <script>
    function submitData()
    {
      fetch("http://localhost:3000/sectionSelection", {
        method: "POST",
        headers: {
          "Accept": "application/json",
          "Content-Type": "application/json"
        },
        body: JSON.stringify({
          email: document.getElementById("email").value,
          name: document.getElementById("name").value
        })
      }).then(response => response.json())
      .then(data => {
        console.log("Success!",data);
      }).catch((error) => {
        console.log("Error",error)
      });
    }
  </script>
  <body>
    <h1>Inspectinator: e-sign</h1>
    <p><strong>
      It's time to complete the inspection process! Please input the client email and name. 
      Upon clicking 'Review and Sign', an email will be sent to your inbox. There, you can 
      submit an e-signature. Upon completion, your client will automatically recieve an 
      e-signature request. You can view the status of both signature requests on the next page.
    </strong></p>
    <p>Email:</p>
    <input type="text" id="email" value="michael37_37@outlook.com"/>
    <p>Name:</p>
    <input type="text" id="name" value="Michaels Twin"/>
    <p></p>
    <form method="POST" enctype = "multipart/form-data">
        <input type="submit" value="Submit" onclick="submitData();"/>
    </form>
    <form action="/signature">
        <input type="submit" value="Review and Sign"/>
    </form>
  </body>
</html>